num_char = len(input("What is your name ")) # taken the length of an integer datatype / using input and length function to determine amount of characters
new_num_char = str(num_char)                # converts the old variable num_char(object) to a string and uses a new variable new_num_char to insert into the string by way of concatenation
                                        
print("Your name has " + new_num_char + " characters. ")    # prints a statement of all the dataypes of all pieces of data, that are being added (concatenated) together are the same datatype strings.